  "assumptions": [
    {
      "claim": "Standard conditions: every dissolved species is at 1 M (unit activity), any gas at 1 bar, and the temperature is 25 °C. The tabulated $E^\\circ$ values — and so $E^\\circ_\\text{cell}$ and $\\Delta G^\\circ$ — hold only there; away from standard conditions the Nernst equation corrects the voltage.",
      "kind": "model"
    },
    {
      "claim": "The standard reduction potentials are measured against the standard hydrogen electrode (defined as exactly 0 V) — a sourced convention. Only differences $E^\\circ_\\text{cathode} - E^\\circ_\\text{anode}$ are physically meaningful (the zero point is arbitrary).",
